Product Details


Wheels and Tires

Hubs: 
                                Front: Scott EC Pro w/20mm through-axle; Rear: Shimano
                            

Tires: 
                                Schwalbe Fat Albert, 26 x 2.4
                            

Spoke Brand: 
                                DT Swiss Champion 1.8mm stainless-steel
                            
Components

Brakeset: 
                                Avid Elixir 5 discs, 203mm front, 185mm rear rotors
                            

Shift Levers: 
                                SRAM X-7
                            

Rear Cogs: 
                                Shimano, 9-speed: 11-34
                            

Saddle: 
                                Scott Ransom
                            

Handlebar: 
                                Scott Pilot 30 Pro
                            

Handlebar Stem: 
                                Scott EC
                            


Factory Description

                                 An all-mountain master of epic proportions, Scott's Ransom 20 tackles the ups and the downs with equal voracity. It boasts a light monocoque aluminum frame with an adjustable rear shock that gives you three suspension modes (locked out, 100mm- and 165mm-travel) for the ultimate in trail domination. For even more bump control, the Ransom features a 160mm-travel RockShox Lyrik R fork, Avid Elixir discs and fat Schwalbe knobbies. Plus, you'll appreciate the smooth-rolling Alex wheels, the quick-shifting SRAM/Shimano drivetrain and Scott's awesome aluminum components. 
                            





























